D’Nyra who is currently gearing up for the release of his debut EP, has just released a music video for his new single “Rain.” The pop anthem dropped August 29. “Rain” talks about the beauty in pain, the strength in perseverance and believe in oneself in face of self-doubt,” D’Nyra said in a statement. As previously reported, the singer/songwriter will debut his first EP album in February 2020. The clip, the video starts off at a desert in Dubai, the sun bearing down as D’Nyra sings all around the desert. Vanguard Upcoming music and voice-over artiste, TerryThe Voice, born Terrence Odenigbo is set to take the music scene by storm with the release of his first EP titled 'Under Surveillance' by middle of October of this year, having announced his arrival on the scene with his debut single 'Prince on my… September 22, 2019 In "Entertainment" The Nigerian entertainment industry enjoyed good music from greenhorns and big shots in the music making craft in 2017. January 6, 2018 In "Music" As the music industry awaits the much-talked about EP of one of   Nigeria’s fast-rising music stars, Adeniyi Ariyo, otherwise known as Phlex, the music sensation has hinted that he would be dropping a new   single ‘Private’ off the new EP, entitled ‘Undaunted’. September 8, 2018 In "Music"